  m_Name: Category Priorities
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Trailback.Demo.Features.Data.FeatureDemoData
  featureName: Category Priorities
  shortDescription: Control which navigation category is resolved first during back
    navigation.
  fullDescription: 'Trailback uses category priorities to determine which navigation
    element should respond when a back navigation request occurs.


    This makes
    it possible to manage multiple UI layers consistently. For example, if a popup
    is open on top of a screen, the popup can be resolved first before navigation
    continues to underlying UI elements.


    Features include:


    * Priority-Based
    Resolution

    * Multi-Layer Navigation Support

    * Popup-First Workflows

    *
    Configurable Navigation Order


    This approach helps keep navigation behavior
    predictable in applications where screens, dialogs, popups, overlays, and other
    UI layers can be active at the same time.'
  screenshots: []
  videoUrl: 
  documentationUrl: https://github.com/akpardeshi/Trailback/#adding-popups-and-priorities
